{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1775812557,"nonce":"TW7en+UZqsg3S/+sAX3Z3SghtDw=","title":"Allow removing all sub-items from a parent item","message":"The parent item edit form hides the 'entfernen' button on Artikel #1 (index 0), preventing removal of the first sub-item. This means you can never go below one item.\n\nDesired behavior: allow removing any item, including the last one, so a parent item can have zero sub-items.\n\nModel impact (low):\n- `app/views/parent_items/_form.html.erb` calls `parent_item.items.first.uid.blank?` in 4 places (lines 140, 143, 149, 208). With zero items, `.first` returns nil and `.uid` raises NoMethodError. Fix: use `items.first\u0026.uid`.\n- Tab selection logic needs a fallback when items is empty (default to 'Unterscheidbare Artikel' tab).\n- The `display:none` style on index 0 needs to be removed.\n- No model validations require items to exist on ParentItem.","files":null}]}